webResources.textAttributionSnippet: (en) Interior of the medieval wooden church in Tidersrum. From the fixtures shown in the picture, one in four chandeliers made of ore from the 1700s and a similar fran the same time made of glass prisms, probably made at Kungsholm’s glass mill. The pulpit in its simple Renaissance style was added in 1661 and painted in the following year by Master Johan Christofersson - https://www.europeana.eu/item/73/S_OM_photo_OMFB000301. AB Flygtrafik. Östergötlands museum - http://digitaltmuseum.se/021016419847. Public Domain Mark - http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/mark/1.0/
